Mrs Alan Johnstone was a Pinchot, sister to  Amos and Gifford.
See NYT article from 1892 at <a href="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9D00E6DA1F31E033A25751C2A9649D94639ED7CF">query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9D00E6DA1F31E033A...</a>
&quot;Miss Antoinette E. Pinchot was married yesterday to the Hon. Alan Johnstone of England Instead of taking place in St. George's Church as originally intended, the ceremony was performed at the home of the bride's parents, Mr. and Mrs. James W. Pinchot of Gramercy Park.&quot;
